text: Izhbuldy () is a rural locality (a village) in Kashkarovsky Selsoviet, Zilairsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 77 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 30 km from Zilair. == References == Category:Rural localities in Zilairsky District
title: Izhbuldy
